<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-09T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-09T03:00:00-05:00" n="542" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4R1/61: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The American Observer at the Conference on the
                                Suppression of Opium Smoking at Bangkok</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-09T15:00:00+07:00">November 9, 1931—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 9—6:43 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Conference was opened by Siamese Minister for Foreign Affairs and after
                            organization adjourned until tomorrow morning when statements of
                            delegates are invited.</p>
                        <p>Siamese Under Secretary of State Foreign Affairs elected President, and
                            Van Wettum, Vice President.</p>
                        <p>China not represented, ostensibly for financial reasons.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>